---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Get Started — Reliquery" description="Set up Reliquery in five minutes: install, sign in, connect your brand documents, and run your first analysis.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-styles">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink">Get started with Reliquery</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink/60 mt-3">Eight steps to get fully set up. Your first brand audit by the end.</p>

    <!-- Step 1: Install -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">1</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Install the extension</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Add Reliquery from the Chrome Web Store. It takes a few seconds and requires no special permissions at install time.
        </p>
        <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/reliquery/kgkpejegjlfcmghgkcebfekdnocgohbi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-lg bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-90 transition">
          Add to Chrome — Free
        </a>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Tip:</strong> After installing, pin Reliquery to your toolbar. Click the puzzle piece icon in Chrome's toolbar, then click the pin next to Reliquery. This makes it one click to open the side panel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2: Sign in -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">2</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Sign in</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Click the Reliquery icon in your toolbar to open the side panel. You'll see a sign-in screen.
        </p>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink/80 list-decimal pl-5">
          <li>Enter your email address and click <strong>Send code</strong></li>
          <li>Check your inbox for a verification code from Reliquery</li>
          <li>Enter the code and click <strong>Verify</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/60">
          Reliquery uses passwordless sign-in. No password to remember — just a one-time code each time you sign in.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3: Brand Reliquary -->
    <div id="create-reliquary" class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start scroll-mt-8">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">3</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Create and connect your Brand Reliquary</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Your Brand Reliquary is the collection of documents that define your brand — voice guidelines, positioning statements, design principles, messaging frameworks, or anything else that captures how your brand should show up. Most teams don't have these in one place yet. That's normal — and it's the whole point.
        </p>

        <!-- Starter template CTA — primary path for most users -->
        <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary bg-primary/5 p-6">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Start from our template</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
            We've built a starter Brand Reliquary with the files most teams need — voice and tone, positioning, visual identity, and approved terminology. Fork the repo (i.e., make your own copy), fill in the blanks with your brand's specifics, and connect it to Reliquery. Takes about 20 minutes.
          </p>
          <a href="https://github.com/SkolKraken/brand-reliquary-starter" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-lg bg-primary px-5 py-2.5 text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-90 transition">
            Fork the starter template on GitHub
          </a>
          <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl bg-white border border-black/10 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink">What's in the template:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li><code>voice-and-tone.md</code> — How your brand sounds (formal vs casual, humor, vocabulary)</li>
              <li><code>positioning.md</code> — What you do, who it's for, and why it matters</li>
              <li><code>visual-identity.md</code> — Colors, typography, imagery guidelines</li>
              <li><code>terminology.md</code> — Approved terms, forbidden words, and common mistakes</li>
              <li><code>mission-and-values.md</code> — The promises your brand actually makes</li>
              <li><code>boilerplate.md</code> — Taglines, one-liners, and elevator pitches</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/60">
              Markdown (<code>.md</code>) files work best. You don't need every file — even a single voice guide will dramatically improve your audits. Start small and add more as you go.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Connect instructions -->
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Connect it to Reliquery</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
          Once your Brand Reliquary exists (forked template or your own repo), open the <strong>Settings</strong> dropdown in the side panel and find the <strong>Connect your Brand Reliquary</strong> card.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">GitHub repository</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              Paste your repository URL and click <strong>Connect</strong>. You can optionally specify a branch and subfolder path. Private repos require a GitHub personal access token with <code>repo</code> (read-only) scope.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Local folder</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              Prefer to keep files on your machine? Click <strong>Choose folder</strong> and select the folder containing your brand documents. Documents are read at analysis time and never uploaded.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4: Home Base -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">4</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Set your Home Base</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Your Home Base is your website's URL. Reliquery uses it to know which pages are yours and which belong to competitors.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          In the <strong>Settings</strong> dropdown, find the <strong>Home Base</strong> card and enter your website URL (e.g. <code>https://yoursite.com</code>).
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> When you're on your own site and click Analyze, Reliquery runs <strong>Audit</strong> mode (brand alignment). When you're on a competitor's site, it runs <strong>Scout</strong> mode (competitive analysis). Home Base is what tells Reliquery which is which.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 5: Permissions -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">5</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Grant page access</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Reliquery needs permission to read the page you're analyzing. It never requests access in the background — you're always in control of which sites it can see.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Recommended: grant access to all sites</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              In the <strong>Settings</strong> dropdown, find the <strong>Page Access</strong> card and click <strong>Permit Reliquery to analyze web pages</strong>. Chrome will ask once whether to allow Reliquery on all sites. After that, you'll never see a permission prompt again.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/60">
              This is the smoothest experience — no interruptions when you switch between your site and a competitor's.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-ink/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Alternative: per-site prompts</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              If you skip the broad grant, Chrome will show a per-site permission dialog the first time you click <strong>Analyze This Page</strong> on each new site. Click <strong>Allow</strong> to proceed. Each grant persists for that site, so you'll only see the prompt once per domain.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Revoking access:</strong> You can disable Reliquery's page access at any time. Open <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Page Access</strong> and click the <strong>Disable</strong> button. You can also manage permissions from <code>chrome://extensions</code> → Reliquery → Site access. Disabling access doesn't uninstall the extension — it just means Reliquery will ask for permission again the next time you analyze a page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 6: First analysis -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">6</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Run your first audit</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Navigate to a page on your website in Chrome. Open the Reliquery side panel, make sure you're on the <strong>Audit</strong> tab, and click <strong>Analyze This Page</strong>.
        </p>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink/80 list-decimal pl-5">
          <li>Reliquery extracts the page content and sends it (along with your brand documents) for analysis</li>
          <li>In about 15–30 seconds, you'll see a brand alignment score, drift findings with citations, and suggested rewrites</li>
          <li>Every finding links back to the specific passage in your Brand Reliquary that it violates, so you always know <em>why</em> something was flagged</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="mt-4 text-ink/80">
          Want to analyze a competitor instead? Switch to the <strong>Scout</strong> tab, navigate to a competitor's page, and click <strong>Analyze This Page</strong>. You'll get a side-by-side competitive breakdown — category claim, voice, pricing — compared against your own positioning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 7: Forge -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">7</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Set up Forge mode</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Forge lets you type a design instruction in plain English — "make the hero CTA more prominent," "swap the color scheme to dark mode" — and Reliquery applies the CSS and HTML changes live to the page. It requires a Pro subscription and your own Anthropic API key.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-6">Getting your API key</h3>
        <ol class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-ink/80 list-decimal pl-5">
          <li>Go to <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary underline">console.anthropic.com</a> and create an account (or sign in)</li>
          <li>Navigate to <strong>API Keys</strong> and create a new key</li>
          <li>Copy the key — you'll only see it once</li>
          <li>In Reliquery, switch to the <strong>Forge</strong> tab and paste your key into the setup field</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary">Privacy and billing</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Your API key is stored locally in your browser (<code>chrome.storage.local</code>) and is <strong>never</strong> transmitted to Reliquery's servers</li>
            <li>Forge requests are proxied through the Reliquery backend so Claude can see the page — your key is included in the outbound request to Anthropic and discarded immediately after</li>
            <li>All Forge usage is billed directly to your own Anthropic account — you can see every request in your Anthropic dashboard</li>
            <li>Revoking the key at <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary underline">console.anthropic.com</a> instantly disables Forge</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Tip:</strong> Set a spend limit in your Anthropic dashboard to control costs. A typical Forge session costs a few cents — the side panel shows the cost of each request in real time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 8: Usage and billing -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex gap-5 items-start">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">8</div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-0.5">Understand your usage and plan</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
          Open the <strong>Account & Usage</strong> dropdown in the side panel to see your current plan and how many analyses you've used.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-ink uppercase tracking-wider">Usage tracker</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              The usage bar shows how many Audit and Scout analyses you've used out of your monthly limit (e.g. <strong>3/5</strong> on the free plan). The bar updates in real time after each analysis. Forge mode doesn't count toward your limit — it uses your own Anthropic key.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Upgrading to Pro</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/80">
              When you're ready for more, click the <strong>Upgrade</strong> button next to the usage bar. This opens a Stripe checkout page in a new tab where you can subscribe to Pro. Your plan activates instantly — no need to reload the extension.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/60">
              Reliquery never sees your payment details. Stripe handles all billing securely. You can manage your subscription, update your payment method, or cancel at any time through Stripe's customer portal.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-ink/70"><strong>Free plan:</strong> 5 Audit + Scout analyses per month. <strong>Pro plan:</strong> 100 analyses per month, plus access to Forge mode. Unused analyses don't roll over.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Help -->
    <div class="mt-16 text-center">
      <p class="text-ink/60 text-sm">
        Stuck? Email <a href="mailto:support@reliquery.app" class="text-primary underline">support@reliquery.app</a>
        or check the <a href="/support" class="text-primary underline">support page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
